    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at some shipping docs for a run from Ningbo to Rotterdam. Can you explain the main differences between CIF and FOB under Incoterms 2020? Specifically, I need to know when the risk of loss actually transfers to us as the buyer.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "CIF (Cost, Insurance, and Freight) and FOB (Free On Board) differ significantly in where the seller's responsibility ends and the buyer's begins. With FOB, the risk transfers to you, the buyer, once the goods are loaded onto the vessel nominated by you at the port of shipment (Ningbo). In contrast, under CIF, the seller bears the risk until the goods are loaded and even arranges and pays for insurance and freight up to the port of destination (Rotterdam).",
      "source": "target",
